<td width=50%><font color=white>Posted By: Serrina</font></td><td width=50% align=right><font color=white>2000-04-08 10:08:31</font></td></tr><tr>
<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>I've never heard it was part of a quest, if it is, probably not a well known one at that. :)<BR>
<BR>
This is better than savant's cap hands down.  Better ac by 3 (I think sav cap is 2, if i'm not mistaken), gives 3 str (though heavy at 5 wt, least str off sets it), can give about 14 more mana for you lvl than a sav's cap.  (thought they at Verant have recently said that depending on total mana you have, plus mana items might not give full bonus, so that twinking plus mana items doesn't help much at lower lvls.  I'd hope by 19, they figure you can have the money at least to buy it and thus the reduction if any would be minimal).  All in all, this is a better piece, and it has metal look, which gives it style points.  And clerics in particular can get beat on pretty hard at times, so all the ac you can get it probably good ac.</font></td></tr></table>
